## üì¶ API Endpoints Documentation

### GET /api/products
Retrieve all products. Supports filtering and pagination. Example: `/api/products?category=electronics&page=1&limit=2`

### GET /api/products/:id
Retrieve a specific product by ID. Example: `/api/products/1`

### POST /api/products
Create a new product. Required JSON body: `{"name": "Tablet", "description": "10-inch tablet", "price": 300, "category": "electronics", "inStock": true}`

### PUT /api/products/:id
Update an existing product. Example: `/api/products/1` Body: `{"price": 1500, "inStock": false}`

### DELETE /api/products/:id
Delete a product by ID. Example: `/api/products/2`

### GET /api/products-search
Search products by name. Example: `/api/products-search?name=laptop`

### GET /api/products-stats
Returns product count grouped by category. Example output: `{"electronics": 2, "kitchen": 1}`

## üß™ Testing
You can test the API using Postman, Insomnia, or curl. Example: `curl http://localhost:3000/api/products`


